<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Submission from the City Growth Commission (CD01)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Submission from the City Growth Commission</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (CD0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">note with interest </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Communities and Local Government Committee’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">inquiry into</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">iscal devolution to cities and city regions.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The City Growth Commission, launched in October 2013, explore</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> similar questions. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Commission </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is an independent and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">authorit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ative inquiry into how best to enable our cities to respond to the fiscal and economic challenges of the future</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, in the context of a global trend towards growth driven by mid-tier cities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Commission will build on the growing consensus in favour of re</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">balancing the economy and dev</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">olving more power to our cities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ask how we can make our cities financially and economically sustainable. It will also ask how growth in other cities can complement London’s economic success and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">look at </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the relationship between devolution, reform and growth strategies in London and in our other cities. In particular, the Commission will focus on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">labour market</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s, skills and investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, issue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of critical importance to the future of our economy. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The ul</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">timate objective of the Commission is to lay the foundations for a significant shift away from the centre and towards cities, and to show the next Government, of whichever party, why this is needed and how it can be achieved. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Commission’s membership </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">consists of:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Jim O’Neill, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Retiring Chairman of Goldman Sachs Asset (Chair)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Greg Clark</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, Chairman, OECD Forum on Local Development Agencies and Investment Strategies and Global Fellow, Metropolitan Programme at The Brookings Institution   </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Diane Coyle OBE</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Chief Executive of Enlightenment Economics and Vice-Chair of the BBC Trust;  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">-</sp