</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Skills and labour markets,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and how to align decision making and funding of skills agendas at local and national level.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Infrastructure, connectivity, and clustering,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> includ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">housing, transport, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">digital</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Fiscal and policy devolution</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">includ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> cities’ freedom to borrow to invest </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and to maximise their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">competitiveness.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Secretariat will be hosted by the RSA, which has run several important and influential Commissions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">For example, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2020 Public Services Commission</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">haired by Sir Andrew Fos</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, was influential in shaping the public service reform agenda prior</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and following – the 2010 election by bringing together </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a range of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">perspectives </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">across the political spectrum, academia, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">public, private and voluntary sectors.   </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Other examples in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">clude the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Academies Commission (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">haired by Christine Gilbert), and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, currently, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Independent Review of the Police Federation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">chaired by Sir David Normington</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">During the course of the Commission’s Inquiry we will publish reports and papers on our findi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ngs as they emerge.  The first of these will be a scene setter looking at the factors which are driving growth in cities globally, and the challenges and opportunities that thes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e throw up for British cities. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In the Spring</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> we will also host some evidence sessions across the country</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, after which w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e anticipate being in a position to discuss some of our emerging findings. If that dovetails with your timescales for oral evidence then I or one of my Commissioner </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">olleagues would</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> be pleased to provide evidence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">at a future hearing of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Communities and Local Government Committee’s inquiry.  </span><a name="_GoBack"></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">I look forward to h